1
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:14,267
No one else knows
about my illness except Greg.

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:17,733
Even my kids have no idea.

3
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:20,333
For once, think about yourself.

4
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:22,367
You like me, too, right?
So this isn't wrong.

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,867
What would be wrong
is letting this chance

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:25,900
for us to be together slip away.

7
00:00:26,033 --> 00:00:28,200
I thought you didn't want
to be reckless?

8
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,300
So why are you the one acting
impulsive and careless now?

9
00:01:20,067 --> 00:01:21,733
So, they're still there?

10
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:24,933
But they already split up.

11
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:27,533
Looks like they fought.

12
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:30,600
Oh my gosh!
That was way too close.

13
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:33,400
Good thing
I caught on right away.

14
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:36,067
<i>Please prepare the keycard.
Could you please hurry up?</i>

15
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,600
<i> Sure, Ma'am.</i>

16
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:43,367
<i> What's bothering you?</i>

17
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:45,233
<i>What were you two talking about?</i>

18
00:01:47,867 --> 00:01:49,633
<i> It just a bit odd.</i>

19
00:01:50,767 --> 00:01:53,467
<i> Marj never asks where I am.</i>

20
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,367
<i> But this time, she did.</i>

21
00:01:57,833 --> 00:01:59,967
<i>What if she's starting to get
suspicious?</i>

22
00:02:03,633 --> 00:02:05,300
<i> Let me see your phone.</i>

23
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:08,167
<i> What?</i>

24
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:10,167
<i>I just need to check something.</i>

25
00:02:28,233 --> 00:02:31,033
<i>Your location is being shared
with her.</i>

26
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:40,767
<i> And why would she do that?</i>

27
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:43,167
<i> This is always turned off.</i>

28
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:46,533
<i>Lalaine and I only turn it on
when we travel abroad,</i>

29
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:48,833
<i> so we don't lose each other.</i>

30
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:53,133
<i>What if Marj
really is suspicious?</i>

31
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:56,900
<i>Maybe she's just waiting
for a chance to catch you.</i>

32
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:00,533
<i> Most likely, she already knows</i>

33
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:02,867
<i>I've been lying
about being at the office.</i>

34
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,067
<i> And I'm actually here.</i>

35
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,167
<i> She might be on her way</i>

36
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:08,633
<i>to confirm whatever shady thing
you're up to.</i>

37
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:14,233
<i> Thea, I can't get caught.</i>

38
00:03:14,367 --> 00:03:15,467
<i>I already have a lot
going on at work.</i>

39
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:16,800
<i>I can't deal with this
on top of everything else.</i>

40
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,467
<i> I have an idea.</i>

41
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:45,167
Good thing you're sharp, friend.

42
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,233
Of course.

43
00:03:46,367 --> 00:03:49,233
I'm smarter and more cunning
than Marj, okay?

44
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,833
Marj. Hey.

45
00:03:58,967 --> 00:04:00,300
Marj!

46
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,200
Marj! Hey.

47
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:06,667
Sorry,
I shouldn't have said anything.

48
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,700
If I hadn't, you wouldn't
be suspicious of Paolo.

49
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,533
Now it has just made things
worse.

50
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:13,200
I didn't do that
because you told me to.

51
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:16,200
I did it
because I had a gut feeling.

52
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:18,767
Do you think it's really true?

53
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:20,067
What if he really just went
to the hotel lounge

54
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,433
because he was tired?

55
00:04:22,567 --> 00:04:26,367
That's exactly how my dad
used to be with my mom.

56
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:30,200
When she questioned him,
he'd get mad.

57
00:04:30,367 --> 00:04:33,200
I know that script by heart.

58
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:36,867
They act like they're the ones
being suffocated.

59
00:04:38,067 --> 00:04:42,033
So many excuses, so much drama.

60
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:44,767
But the truth is,
they're hiding a lot.

61
00:04:46,633 --> 00:04:49,300
Getting mad
is their defense mechanism.

62
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:51,600
So you stop asking questions.

63
00:04:57,433 --> 00:04:59,167
I just have this feeling.

64
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,200
Paolo is hiding something.

65
00:05:14,067 --> 00:05:18,233
- Let's take this off now.
- It's okay.

66
00:05:18,367 --> 00:05:20,567
- I'm a good boy.
- Yes.

67
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:23,133
- I love you.
- I love you, Mom.

68
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:26,800
You're such a good boy.

69
00:05:26,933 --> 00:05:30,267
- We'll head home in a bit.
- Evelyn?

70
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,433
What you saw...

71
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:50,900
nobody was supposed to see that.

72
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:54,033
But I saw what you did.

73
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:59,067
You helped me.

74
00:06:00,467 --> 00:06:02,300
Thank you...

75
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:04,033
Evelyn.

76
00:06:23,733 --> 00:06:25,867
I have alopecia.

77
00:06:30,467 --> 00:06:33,000
It started years ago,

78
00:06:33,133 --> 00:06:36,067
when I found out
Greg was cheating on me.

79
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,600
The stress...

80
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:44,200
it ate me alive.

81
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:49,967
Little by little,

82
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:52,233
my hair started falling out.

83
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:56,067
And then one day,

84
00:06:57,767 --> 00:07:00,600
Greg stopped being intimate
with me.

85
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:08,133
The way he looked at me changed.

86
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:12,900
Maybe...q

87
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,300
he thinks...

88
00:07:15,467 --> 00:07:17,200
I'm ugly now.

89
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:27,267
No one else knows about my
condition except Greg and Yolly.

90
00:07:29,667 --> 00:07:32,467
Even my kids...

91
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,800
have no idea.

92
00:07:37,567 --> 00:07:39,967
Evelyn,

93
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:44,500
my husband has already
fallen out of love with me.

94
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:52,933
I don't want to lose my dignity,
too.

95
00:07:55,433 --> 00:08:00,500
And I don't want
my children to pity me.

96
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:15,267
Thank you.

97
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:22,400
Thank you.

98
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,367
Ma'am, do you need anything?

99
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,267
I just want
to ask you something, Oscar.

100
00:08:48,033 --> 00:08:51,500
Were you the one who drove Paolo
to the hotel earlier?

101
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:52,933
No, Ma'am.

102
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:58,233
But Sir Paolo seemed troubled.

103
00:08:58,367 --> 00:08:59,800
He said he wanted to be alone.

104
00:08:59,933 --> 00:09:03,667
So when he asked to borrow
the car keys, I just let him.

105
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:07,267
Or could he be meeting
another woman?

106
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,633
Has he said anything to you?

107
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:18,800
Nothing, Ma'am. Sir Paolo
has changed a long time ago.

108
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:22,833
I haven't seen him fool around
ever since you got married.

109
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:28,367
Thank you, Oscar.

110
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:10,467
Jobert, take your vitamins first
before you play, okay?

111
00:10:10,733 --> 00:10:12,767
- Yes, Mom.
- Good boy.

112
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:13,833
Here.

113
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,433
That's good.

114
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,467
Drink some water.

115
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,533
- Evelyn.
- Drink plenty of water.

116
00:10:21,667 --> 00:10:22,833
Evelyn.

117
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:26,867
Oh, look at this.

118
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,067
Pick something from here.
I've only used these once.

119
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,267
Go ahead, choose.

120
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:35,400
Oh, you don't have
to do this for me.

121
00:10:35,567 --> 00:10:36,900
I know. But I want to.

122
00:10:37,033 --> 00:10:39,100
Come on, go ahead.
Pick something.

123
00:10:39,233 --> 00:10:40,267
Go on.

124
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,167
That's nice.

125
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:45,600
And you can use this one
especially with pants.

126
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:47,033
- Thank you.
- See? They're all so pretty.

127
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:48,767
Go ahead.

128
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,133
Regina?

129
00:10:50,267 --> 00:10:52,800
- Evelyn?
- Yes, hon?

130
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:55,833
Is this for real?
Are you two getting along now?

131
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:57,333
Honestly, I was surprised, too.

132
00:10:57,467 --> 00:10:59,200
But you know what,

133
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,833
I realized
Evelyn's actually pretty great.

134
00:11:00,967 --> 00:11:02,567
She's trustworthy.

135
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:06,133
So go ahead, pick something.
That'll look good on you.

136
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:07,733
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

137
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:10,567
That'll look really
nice with jeans.

138
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:57,500
Dad, please.

139
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:01,200
Just give me time.
I'll fix this.

140
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:04,767
Did he change
the password?

141
00:12:11,167 --> 00:12:12,567
Fix it?

142
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:17,300
Do you really think I'd still
trust you with a project?

143
00:12:29,267 --> 00:12:31,833
I already talked
to majority of the board.

144
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:35,400
We've decided...

145
00:12:35,533 --> 00:12:37,733
that Aldrin will take over
the Menagerie.

146
00:12:37,867 --> 00:12:41,133
- The whole project.
- What, Dad?

147
00:12:41,267 --> 00:12:44,133
He's already working
on damage control.

148
00:12:44,367 --> 00:12:46,000
He's cleaning up your mess.

149
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:52,767
No.

150
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:56,733
Dad, that's my project.
It's mine!

151
00:12:56,867 --> 00:13:02,100
I gave it to you
since I thought you were ready.

152
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:03,533
Turns out,

153
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:06,267
I handed a fully loaded company
to a boy

154
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,633
who still needs supervision.

155
00:13:08,767 --> 00:13:12,567
Now I have to protect
the company.

156
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,067
Something you failed to do.

157
00:13:45,367 --> 00:13:51,367
Instead of helping my husband,
I ended up doubting him.

158
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,733
I am doubting him without a
proof.

159
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:56,367
I know what you're going through
is hard.

160
00:13:56,533 --> 00:13:59,333
What you're going through is
hard.

161
00:13:59,467 --> 00:14:03,333
Especially if it's true
that Paolo has another woman.

162
00:14:04,433 --> 00:14:07,567
But if you don't have proof,

163
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:09,300
don't pick a fight with him.

164
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:17,200
I should stop being suspicious.

165
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,767
I should focus
on how I can help Paolo.

166
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:24,233
How I can be a good wife.

167
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,700
Marj,

168
00:14:28,867 --> 00:14:31,300
your husband
needs you right now.

169
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:34,800
So...

170
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:38,500
go to your room.
Be there for him.

171
00:14:39,433 --> 00:14:42,533
Figure out
how you can support him.

172
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:50,533
Love you, Mom.

173
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,967
Good night, Mom.

174
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,133
Good night, Jobert.

175
00:14:58,267 --> 00:15:00,500
Sleep well, okay?

176
00:15:00,633 --> 00:15:02,400
- Good night.
- Good night.

177
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:43,667
Darn it!

178
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,167
Pao...

179
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,567
Love...

180
00:16:12,933 --> 00:16:15,233
I'm sorry.

181
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:20,333
Why won't you...

182
00:16:20,467 --> 00:16:22,267
maybe try making it up
to your dad?

183
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:24,100
Do you want me to help you?

184
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:28,600
How?

185
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:31,700
He replaced me.

186
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:35,267
How am I supposed to make it up
to him

187
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,167
if he already took away
my chance?

188
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,900
And you, how are you supposed
to help me?

189
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:44,433
You don't even trust me.

190
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:46,000
Love, I'm sorry.

191
00:16:46,133 --> 00:16:49,367
I'm sorry I didn't trust you.

192
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:53,533
I was wrong to doubt you,
and I should stop doubting you.

193
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:55,867
Especially after seeing
how exhausted

194
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:00,833
and preoccupied you've been
with work. I'm so sorry.

195
00:17:00,967 --> 00:17:03,267
So you believe me now?

196
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:46,267
Evelyn?

197
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:51,267
How did you know I was here?

198
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,200
I checked your room,

199
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:54,633
and you weren't there.

200
00:17:54,767 --> 00:17:56,500
So I assumed that you're here.

201
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:05,533
What's wrong?

202
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:12,233
Are you still stressing over
your husband?

203
00:18:12,367 --> 00:18:14,833
It just hurts to think...

204
00:18:16,567 --> 00:18:19,433
about how it's so easy for him

205
00:18:19,567 --> 00:18:22,833
to fall in love over
and over again.

206
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:27,767
While it's only ever been him
for me.

207
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:29,233
I've never thought
about anyone else,

208
00:18:29,367 --> 00:18:31,733
never loved anyone else...

209
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:34,700
but him.

210
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:38,400
Stop thinking about that man.
He's stupid.

211
00:18:38,533 --> 00:18:41,667
You didn't lose anything.
He did.

212
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:43,133
Because...

213
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:49,133
he doesn't even realize
how special you are.

214
00:18:49,267 --> 00:18:50,767
If you want...

215
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:56,300
you could do the same thing
your husband's doing.

216
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:57,567
You can have me.

217
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:02,500
Give me a chance.
I'll shower you with love.

218
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:07,567
More than
you've ever dreamed of.

219
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:09,400
Greg, please.

220
00:19:09,533 --> 00:19:10,633
Please.

221
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:14,467
Let me give you the love
you deserve.

222
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:19,367
Greg, I'm no different from the
women my husband cheated with

223
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,800
if I take you away
from your wife.

224
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:26,633
And besides, Greg,
I can't do that to Regina.

225
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:30,400
She's been nothing but kind
to me.

226
00:19:30,567 --> 00:19:33,133
Greg, I don't want to destroy
our family.

227
00:19:33,267 --> 00:19:36,333
Stop thinking about other people
for a second.

228
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:39,300
For once, think about yourself.

229
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:43,067
About what will make you happy.

230
00:19:45,467 --> 00:19:47,267
You like me, too, right?

231
00:19:49,333 --> 00:19:51,833
So this isn't wrong.

232
00:19:51,967 --> 00:19:53,433
What would be wrong,

233
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:57,133
is letting this chance for us
to be together slip away.

234
00:20:48,133 --> 00:20:51,167
What is it, Paolo?
You shocked me.

235
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:59,500
Sorry, I had to wait for Marj
to fall asleep.

236
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:00,733
Same here,

237
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:03,567
I waited for Edward to fall
asleep before sneaking out.

238
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:07,900
What do you want to tell me?
Why didn't you just text me?

239
00:21:12,433 --> 00:21:15,033
This?
Do you think you can text this?

240
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,333
Don't you miss this?

241
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:35,800
I thought you didn't want
to be reckless?

242
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:38,933
So why are you the one being
impulsive and careless now?

243
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:43,767
I just want to forget
all the problems at the company.

244
00:21:43,933 --> 00:21:45,367
You know,
something to help me sleep.

245
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,100
By doing this?

246
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:54,667
Why?

247
00:21:54,800 --> 00:22:02,167
This is what you want, too,
right?

248
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:05,433
Wait, what if someone sees us?

249
00:22:05,567 --> 00:22:07,067
If you don't want this,
I'll just go back.

250
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,200
Shut up.

251
00:22:08,667 --> 00:22:09,400
Come with me.

252
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:27,900
Love?

253
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:05,233
Love?

254
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,967
Love?

255
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:10,900
Love?

256
00:24:56,467 --> 00:24:57,533
Mom!

257
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:12,333
Mom, are you okay?

258
00:25:12,467 --> 00:25:13,933
How can I be okay?

259
00:25:14,067 --> 00:25:17,700
I just found out
my husband is cheating again.

260
00:25:17,833 --> 00:25:19,133
Did you catch him?

261
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:22,200
This isn't the first time
I've cheated on Regina.

262
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:25,067
Everyone in this household knows
it.

263
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:27,133
And they don't have a choice
but to accept it.

264
00:25:27,267 --> 00:25:28,333
You know why?

265
00:25:28,467 --> 00:25:30,967
Because I have them
all under my thumb.

266
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:36,233
What's going on here?

267
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:41,700
I found an expensive gift
among Greg's things.

268
00:25:41,833 --> 00:25:44,867
A diamond tennis bracelet

269
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,600
from the same jewelry store
he goes to

270
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:50,533
whenever he has a new fling.

271
00:25:50,667 --> 00:25:52,633
Hey, what's this?

272
00:25:52,767 --> 00:25:53,967
Is this a gift?

273
00:25:54,100 --> 00:25:58,933
Yes, good brother's dad
gave it to Mom.
